  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "This is a screenshot from FFVIIR a solid HDR game. \n\nThis image may
    appear unusually dark for the game, but it is not modified. The game uses Exposure
    volumes so if you angle the camera so it's just enough outside, while inside
    a building the exposure will adjust to outside making the inside too dark. Don't
    worry about it too much...\n\nThe point is this is a good demonstration of colorbanding,
    as one of the scenarios where color banding is most visible is darker scenes.
    \n\nToggle the markers to see the highlighted areas where color banding is most
    prominant, and toggle HDR to swap the images between HDR and SDR versions. \n\nThe
    SDR version you will see larger color sections where there should be smooth shading,
    this is due to the limited color space of HDR. You can also see this by using
    the \"Display HDR\" toggle to turn off the games HDR. This will make the HDR
    version of the image SDR to further prove this color banding.\n\nthe only solution
    for color banding like this in SDR is things like filmgrain and dithering.\n\nLike
    in the other demo how much you see this can depend on display quality and screen
    size. Your display calibration may also be too dark to see aything at all. But
    I assure you a solid degree of visibility is here. "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
