  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "In my opinion this is a core reason why HDR is mandatory, displays are
    getting larger and cheaper. And IMO having one big display is much more manageable
    than many, much like how a single GPU replaced multiple GPU's for gaming. As
    screens get larger and brighter color banding can be more obvious. \n\nThis also
    benefits dark games, Batman, Alan Wake, and more. If you're someone who hates
    film grain you may also see color banding more as film grain often mitigates
    color bandaning. \n\nThe use of HDR will allow games to be both darker and brighter."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
